POLOKWANE – Voting for Kwêla’s Dorp van die Jaar competition is now open and Haenertsburg needs your vote. Known for its variety of markets, restaurants and hiking trails, the picturesque town was chosen as Limpopo’s finalist for Dorp van die Jaar on July 4. Those looking for adventure regularly flock to the town, while bird watchers with their binoculars and hikers make use of the multitude of hiking trails. Famous restaurants include The Pot and Plow, Iron Crown Pub and Bistro and Zwakala Breweries. All these interesting places put Haenertsburg in the spotlight when KykNet’s Kwêla Dorp van die Jaar team had to choose one town in Limpopo to be part of the competition. The winner of the competition will win a 45-second marketing video worth R1m which will be aired on KykNet as well as a big party sponsored by Kia to be featured on Kwêla. Voting opened on July 17 and will close midday on July 22. To vote text HAENERTSBURG to 33157 at R1.50 per SMS. Only 30 SMS per number. 